tspan.tspan: Stakeholder Mapping is a process of collectively identifying the
key stakeholders relating to a project. The three step process
involves identifying all individuals who have an interest in the
project outcome, grouping them, finding connections and
deciding what matters for each. Stakeholder Mapping helps
you ensure you have the right representation of voices.
01. Make a List of All Stakeholders
Individually, start by identifying people involved with or
impacted by the project. Make sure to include specific names
and roles.
02. Cluster Them Into Org Groups
Come together as a team and make sure you have all of your
stakeholders documented. Together decide how to cluster them
in departments or teams. Label the groups.
03. Show Connections and Explain What Matters
Draw lines with arrows connecting the people as well as
between groups. Discuss and write what matters to each
group.
04. Reflect on the Mapping
Identify any emerging themes. Who stands out? What
relationships stand out? Make sure to include stakeholders
missing from your current project reviews.
